Update `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/sdk-event-mapper.ts` to distinguish error results from success results.

## Changes

### 1. Import ErrorCategory type

Add to the imports at the top of the file:

```typescript
import type { ErrorCategory } from '@dorkos/shared/schemas';
```

(Verify the exact import path — it may be `@dorkos/shared/types` depending on how the barrel re-exports. Check the existing imports in the file for the pattern used.)

### 2. Add mapErrorCategory helper

Add this function at module scope, before the `mapSdkMessage` generator function:

```typescript
/** Map SDK result subtypes to user-facing error categories. */
function mapErrorCategory(subtype: string): ErrorCategory {
  switch (subtype) {
    case 'error_max_turns':
      return 'max_turns';
    case 'error_during_execution':
      return 'execution_error';
    case 'error_max_budget_usd':
      return 'budget_exceeded';
    case 'error_max_structured_output_retries':
      return 'output_format_error';
    default:
      return 'execution_error';
  }
}
```

### 3. Replace the result handler block

The current result handler (lines 127-148) always yields `session_status` + `done`. Replace the entire `if (message.type === 'result')` block with:

```typescript
if (message.type === 'result') {
  const result = message as Record<string, unknown>;
  const usage = result.usage as Record<string, unknown> | undefined;
  const modelUsageMap = result.modelUsage as
    | Record<string, Record<string, unknown>>
    | undefined;
  const firstModelUsage = modelUsageMap ? Object.values(modelUsageMap)[0] : undefined;

  // Always emit session_status with final cost/token/model data
  yield {
    type: 'session_status',
    data: {
      sessionId,
      model: result.model as string | undefined,
      costUsd: result.total_cost_usd as number | undefined,
      contextTokens: usage?.input_tokens as number | undefined,
      contextMaxTokens: firstModelUsage?.contextWindow as number | undefined,
    },
  };

  // Emit error event if the result is an error subtype
  const subtype = result.subtype as string | undefined;
  if (subtype && subtype !== 'success') {
    const errors = result.errors as string[] | undefined;
    const category = mapErrorCategory(subtype);
    yield {
      type: 'error',
      data: {
        message: errors?.[0] ?? 'An unexpected error occurred.',
        code: subtype,
        category,
        details: errors?.join('\n'),
      },
    };
  }

  // Always emit done to trigger client cleanup
  yield {
    type: 'done',
    data: { sessionId },
  };
}
```

**Key behavior:**
- `session_status` always emits first (even failed queries have cost/token data)
- `error` emits between `session_status` and `done` only when `subtype !== 'success'`
- `done` always emits last to reset client streaming state
- The error `message` field uses `errors[0]` from the SDK, falling back to `'An unexpected error occurred.'`
- The `details` field joins all error strings with newlines for the collapsible details UI
- Unknown subtypes default to `execution_error` category (defensive)

## Acceptance Criteria

- Success results (`subtype: 'success'`) yield exactly 2 events: `session_status`, `done`
- Error results (`subtype: 'error_during_execution'`, etc.) yield exactly 3 events: `session_status`, `error`, `done`
- The `error` event includes `message`, `code`, `category`, and `details` fields
- `mapErrorCategory` correctly maps all four SDK subtypes
- `pnpm typecheck` passes

